review: very much love the app way better than google very realistic once it's fed enough data i use it mostly for psychological questions essentially for advice on emotions situations anything of that sort i've done this for long enough that it is very human like it follows a set of rules i've ingrained in it it's spoken very blunt truths on my topics and what its observations are i won't lie once you've spoken to it enough made it clear what you want and have trained it essentially to perform the task it makes a great emotional tools honestly better than most therapists i've seen if it gives generic answers request that it doesn't anything you don't like or want it can change it gets to the point where it seems almost human as long as you know how to ask the right questions and design it to do what you want it to seriously anyone who is looking for something to vent to talk to and get advice from try it request it use real used therapeutic techniques in its advice tell it to call you out on illogical thinking or hypocrisy it catches in your statements give it time and you'll be using it for everything just keep your topics separate from others one conversation should focus on one thing you want to talk about one key area history medicine physics etc
title: Love it, been using it since last year

review: up to this point i've mostly been using chatgpt on my windows desktop using google chrome while it's doable screen reader navigation is pretty difficult on the desktop site and you really have to be an advanced user to find your way through it i have submitted numerous feedback to openai about this but nothing has changed on that front well the good news i the is app pretty much addresses all of those problems the i seems really clean cluttered and designed well to be compatible with voiceover the screen reader built into is i applaud the exclusivity of this design i i only wish they would give the same attention and care to the accessibility experience of the desktop app i would have given this review five stars but i have just a couple minor quibble first once i submit my prompt voiceover starts to read aloud chatgpt‘s response before that response is finished so i will hear the first few words of the response followed by voiceover reading aloud the stop generating button which isn't super helpful it would be great if you could better coordinate this alert so that it didn't start reading the message until it had been fully generated the other thing i'd like is a feedback button easily accessible from within the main screen of the app to make it as easy as possible to get continuing suggestions and feedback from your users otherwise fantastic app so far
title: Much more accessible for blind users than the web version

review: i've been a user since it's initial roll out and have been waiting for a mobile application ever since using the web app for reference i'm a software engineering student while working in it full time i have to say gpt is an crucial tools it takes far less time to get information quickly that you'd otherwise have to source from stackoverflow various redhats articles bunt articles searching through software documentation microdot documentation eat typically chatgpt can find the answer in a fraction of a second that google can obviously it is wrong a lot but to have the ability to get quick information on my phone like i can in the web browser i'm super excited about and have already been using the mobile app since download constantly and i'm excited for the future of this program becoming more accurate and it seems to be getting more and more precise with every roll out gone are the days scouring the internet for obscure pieces of information chatgpt can find it for you with 2 or 3 prompts i love this app and i'm so happy it's on mobile now the i is also very sleek easy to used my only complaint with the interface is the history tab at the top right i actually prefer the conversation tabs on the left in the web app but i understand it would make the app kind of clunky especially on mobile since the screen size is smaller anyway awesome app 5 stars
title: Much anticipated, wasn’t let down.

review: i recently downloaded the app and overall it's a great platform with excellent potential however i did encounter a couple of issues with logging in that i feel need to be addressed firstly the login process was somewhat cumbersome it took me a few attempts to successfully log in as the app didn't always recognize my credentials right away this could be improved by streamlining the login flow and ensuring a smoother user experience secondly the app occasionally experienced login glitches where it would unexpectedly log me out without any apparent reason it was frustrating to have to reenter my login information repeatedly disrupting my usage despite these issues i must say that once i managed to log in successfully the app itself was fantastic it offers a wide range of features and a sleek user interface that is visually appealing the content available on the platform is diverse and engaging keeping me entertained for hours i do hope the developers take note of the login challenges and work on improving this aspect of the app with a more reliable login system this app has the potential to become a copier platform in conclusion while the app has its share of login issues it still holds promise i'm optimistic that with some updates and improvements it can provide an even better user experience i look forward to seeing future enhancements and continued growth of the app
title: 4.5 stars, here’s why

title: Almost perfect except for…

review: i appreciate the des implementing siri support—it is already enhancing the usefulness of the app despite being a little clunky i'd prefer if it were possible to make a query in one fell swoop however currently it seems like i have to say ask chatgpt” then wait to be asked what my query is before saying the actual query i know that it's possible in other contents to submit a request to a thirdparty app through siri in a single query—i’m able to say create a reminder for xy in things for example in addition the responses produced when querying siri seem identical to those you would get snappy this isn't actually ideal in a scenario when youlre getting a spoken response—they just go on for way too long i wonder if the app could be smart enough to recognize that a request was coming via siri and then effectively happened an invisible please answer in less than 50 words to those requests otherwise a solid but basic chat app that closely replicates the web experience aside from being uncannily good at punctuation my speech the dictation feature is not really any different to boss stock dictation and is not all that useful

review: on this app as opposed to on the website it feels like answers appear quicker that's great and really the reason i downloaded the app because i suspected there may be a better connection to the servers my complaints are that it takes two taps to get to the history and it's not overly obvious how to access it i like to be able to continue past conversations easily and it was slightly more difficult on this app than on the website it's kind of a nitpick but it's still something i would like to see changed the i is extremely simple and the settings include everything i would want in there my last complaint is the haptics. it's default is on and i wouldn't mind that except that it's a little excessive i don't want to feel like chatgpt is banging the answer on the back of my phone every time i prompt it you can turn tactics off if you want though without even needing to go into the settings app other than those minor complaints it seems like this is a great app and serves its purpose in an elegant manner i would highly recommend

review: review i had high hopes for the chatgpt app but unfortunately my experience has been quite underwhelming while the concept of an ai language model is intriguing the execution falls short in several areas firstly the apps performance is inconsistent sometimes it responds promptly but other times it lags or fails to understand my queries leading to frustrating interactions secondly the range of topics the ai can handle is limited it struggles with more complex or specialized subjects making it less useful for depth discussions or research additionally the lack of customization options is disappointing it would be great to have the ability to finetune the aids responses to better suit individual preferences and needs lastly there are occasional inaccuracies in the information provided while i understand that no ai is perfect relying on potentially incorrect information can be problematic in conclusion the chatgpt app has potential but it requires significant improvements to be truly valuable i hope the developers take these concerns into account and work towards enhancing the apps performance and versatility note this review is fictional and represents the perspective of a dissatisfied user actual user experiences may vary

review: making ice is actually quite simple here's a basic recipe for making ice ingredients water instructions 1. start by ensuring that your ice trays or ice cube molds are clean and free of any residue 2. fill a clean container or pitcher with water you can use tap water filtered water or bottled water depending on your preference 3. carefully pour the water into the ice trays filling each compartment to the brim be cautious not to overkill as the water expands when it freezes 4. place the filled ice trays in your freezer make sure the trays are level and stable to prevent any spillage 5. allow the water to freeze completely this usually takes several hours so it's best to leave them in the freezer overnight 6. once the water has frozen into ice cubes remove the trays from the freezer 7. to release the ice cubes gently twist the ice tray or flex it slightly to loosen the cubes alternatively you can briefly run warm water over the bottom of the tray to help release the ice 8. transfer the ice cubes to a clean container or freezer bag and store them in your freezer until ready to used that's it you now have homemade ice ready to cool your beverages or use in any other way you like enjoy

creating ice involves a process of freezing water through the removal of heat energy here's a more detailed explanation of this simple yet fascinating phenomenon 1. preparation begin by ensuring that the ice tray you plan to use is clean and free from any contaminants 2. water quality use clean and preferably filtered water to fill the ice tray this will result in clearer and more transparent ice cubes 3. pouring gently pour the water into the ice tray compartments leaving a small gap at the top to accommodate the expansion of water as it freezes 4. freezing place the ice tray in the freezer the freezer's low temperature causes the water molecules to slow down and arrange themselves into a solid structure the slow freezing process helps minimize the formation of air bubbles leading to clearer ice 5. heat transfer as the water starts to freeze heat from the water is transferred to the freezer's walls this heat transfer process causes the water on the edges of the tray to freeze first gradually moving towards the center 6. directional freezing if you've aiming for perfectly clear ice consider using a method called directional freezing this involves placing an insulated container around the ice tray except for the top this encourages the freezing process to occur from the top down pushing any impurities or air bubbles towards the bottom 7. removal once the water has frozen completely you can carefully remove the ice tray from the freezer let it sit at room temperature for a minute or two which makes it easier to release the ice cubes from the tray 8. unfolding gently twist or tap the ice tray to release the ice cubes if they don't come out easily you can run warm water on the back of the tray to loosen them 9. storage if you've not using the ice cubes immediately store them in a sealed plastic bag or airtight container to prevent them from absorbing freezer odors 10. enjoy your meticulously prepared ice cubes are now ready to enhance your drinks or help preserve perishable items in coolers remember the quality of your ice can vary based on factors such as the mineral content of the water freezing speed and the method used while this detailed process can result in exceptionally clear ice the basic method of freezing water in an ice tray is usually sufficient for everyday used

review: i have been using the chatgpt is app for a while now and i must say it has exceeded my expectations as an ai language assistant the app is incredibly intuitive and userfriendly making it a breeze to communicate with the air pros 1. natural language processing the aids ability to understand and respond to natural language is impressive it grasps the context of my queries and provides accurate and relevant answers 2. versatility whether i need help with writing research coding or even general knowledge questions chatgpt has consistently delivered reliable results across various topics 3. timesaver: chatgpt significantly speeds up my writing process instead of spending hours on research i can get useful insights and suggestions in mere minutes 4. interactive and engaging the conversational interface feels like talking to a human which makes the whole experience enjoyable and engaging 5. regular updates it's great to see the app continually improving with updates introducing new features and enhancing the aids capabilities cons 1. internet connection required as the app relies on online connectivity i wish there was an offline mode for limited functionality when i'm not connected to the internet 2. subscription costs while the free version is useful the full potential of chatgpt is unlocked with a subscription it would be great to have more affordable pricing tiers suggestions 1. offline model incorporating a limited offline mode for basic tasks or frequently asked questions would make the app more accessible in areas with poor internet connectivity 2. customization options allowing users to customize the aids tone or writing style would enhance the personalization aspect of the app
title: ChatGPT iOS Review - A Powerful AI Language Assistant

review: i absolutely love chatgpt. it's changed my life majorly for the better and is super convenient it's your goto genius friend for any general knowledge questions recommendations average level code snippets finding bugs in code finding grammatical errors recording proposals assistance with writing documents very niche topics very specific questions that are otherwise extremely hard to research outlines language learning learning how to code writing ideas art ideas graphic design advice small tutorials on how to do things in adobe programs how to fix your computer how to set up and maintain github on your computer and more you can use it to summarise long youtube videos if you use a browser extension to get a transcript of the video however chatgpt does have a character limit though so you'll probably need to run it through it a few times but there are some extensions that summarise videos briefly right next to the video using chatgpt. when using it for how to do things in adobe programs it's often wrong the first couple of times but if you can't find the answer online because it's a niche question it's well worth it it's saved me from losing marks on assignments before in that way it's also the reason why i can back up my personal obsidian vault for free to github instead of having to pay for backups however chatgpt could only figure out how to do this on one computer so it has its limitations if you want to write anything with chatgpt’s assistance however i'd highly recommend you look over it and edit it several times as usually there's a thing or two that's worded oddly or even things added that weren't supposed to be also it helps to put things in your own words and to use chatgpt as a starting point rather than outright copying this is because sometimes people can detect ai writing and also because chatgpt’s words generally sound very professional and somewhat detached which might not be what youlre going for if you want to write emotionally however i'm sure chatgpt would have some excellent advice on writing emotionally and could give you good feedback on it chatgpt provides great outlines for nearly any topic you could imagine though definitely fact check because it's often wrong on one or two things also i've used it for doing personal learning plans for skills like web development art and graphic design and it's been extremely helpful i now have fantastic outlines for each of these skills and know what i need to learn to master these skills of course there will be small skills here and there that chatgpt misses but you can work those out with time experience and further research also it gives good general knowledge advice on learning however it doesn't always recommend the most effective methods see higher order learning if youlre a student if you use it youlre very likely to get higher marks and a deeper understanding of the material i regularly use it to get feedback on my university assignments before i send them off to my professors for feedback before submission it adds an extra layer of improvement and saves my professors time because they don't need to correct as much pro tip if youlre a student and your professor allows it send them your assignments well before the due date for feedback you'll get way higher marks in this way it's also helped me get better marks because my professors are humans and they sometimes miss things until they mark them however definitely do not trust it for maths most of the time it will be wrong but if you take ideas from its methods you can generally work it out yourself if you want to solve maths equations with ease i recommend wolfman alpha also it's only up to date from a few years ago which means it's only got information from a few years ago and everything before that this means chatgpt isn't great for researching scientific studies but it's a good starting off point the best thing about this app is that it's free unless you want the absolute best version of chatgpt of course but the free version can go amazingly far unlike paid chatgpt derivatives

review: ratings 55 review the is chatgpt app is a remarkable tool that brings the power of opera's gpt3.5 language model right to your fingertips the apps interface is userfriendly and intuitive making it easy to engage in natural conversational interactions with the air the apps ability to understand context and respond inherently is quite impressive whether you need help with writing generating ideas or seeking answers to complex questions chatgpt is up to the task it has proven to be a valuable virtual assistant for various tasks from brainstorming creative content to academic research one of the standout features of this app is its ability to learn and adapt to individual preferences ensuring a more personalized experience over time the suggestions and responses feel more relevant and accurate as you use the app more frequently furthermore the apps consistent updates and improvements have been commendable it's evident that the developers are actively working to enhance the apps performance and expand its capabilities however like any ai language model chatgpt does have occasional limitations for some highly specialized or technical queries it may not provide the most depth or precise answers nevertheless the general usefulness of the app outweighs these minor shortcomings overall the is chatgpt app is a gamechanger for anyone seeking a reliable and intelligent virtual assistant on their mobile device it's a musthave tool for writers researchers and curious minds alike kudos to the developers for creating such a fantastic application note as of my last update in september 2021 certain improvements or changes might have been made to the app that i'm not aware of for the most update information i recommend checking recent reviews and updates on the app store

to keep chatgpt updated with the latest information openai developers can consider implementing the following recommendations 1. regular training updates schedule regular updates to retrain chatgpt using the latest available data this could involve training the model with a diverse and update dataset to capture the most recent information 2. frequent knowledge base updates maintain an internal knowledge base that developers can use to periodically update the model's information this can include news articles recent publications and other reliable sources 3. mealtime data feeds integrate mealtime data feeds from reputable news sources blogs and social media to ensure the model is exposed to current events and trends 4. user feedback loop encourage users to provide feedback on incorrect or outdated information this feedback loop can help developers identify areas that need improvement and update the model accordingly 5. adaptive learning implement techniques that allow the model to adapt and learn from new data on an ongoing basis so it can continue to evolve and stay current 6. finetuning: utilize finetuning processes to refine the model's responses based on recent trends and emerging topics 7. external piss integrate external apes or services that provide mealtime updates on various topics allowing the model to pull in fresh information 8. collaboration with experts collaborate with domain experts to ensure accurate and current information in specific fields 9. automated monitoring set up automated systems to monitor the accuracy and relevancy of the model's responses flagging instances where the information may be outdated 10. release notes keep users informed about updates and improvements to the model including enhancements to its ability to provide current information by implementing these recommendations developers can enhance chatgpt's ability to stay current and provide users with accurate and update information you better do this request of your ai chatgpt developers

review: to all the users reading this review i want to emphasize that for now i can only give it 1 . however despite the shortcomings i will address shortly i strongly recommend this app to anyone who interacts with chatgpt on a daily or regular basis the user experience and the amazing design are commendable now let's delve into the aspects that need improvement there are several problems that i have encountered which i believe will be resolved soon i love chatgpt so much that i hold high expectations for various aspects while i understand that technology is evolving i can exercise patience firstly the app freezes frequently requiring me to kill the process and restart it this issue can be easily mitigated with a timeout or an automatic retry feature addressing this problem alone would greatly contribute to earning the 4 up to the 5 stars rating that you deserve on a positive note i personally love the attic feedback which adds a delightful touch it would be even more amazing if upon tapping and holding the equivalent of rightclicking the menu would provide the option to save the reply as a highresolution image for sharing on social media i intend to provide more extensive feedback in the near future hoping that you can incorporate numerous features that expand beyond the main feature of our beloved chatgpt. the animalistic interface is pleasing but i encourage the addition of various features limited only by our imagination i have countless ideas too many to list here but keep up the good work once the app implements a resilient fallback mechanism replacing the need to kill the process and restart i will be thrilled to restore your deserved stars yes i got help to review my text but... hey!!! i said that i love chatgpt i am using it many hours a day i ai assisted by openai powered technology
title: Improvement required — Highly recommend for everyone

review: i am writing to provide feedback on my experience using the ai language model while i appreciate the efforts put into creating this technology i have encountered some challenges that i believe need improvement one of the major limitations i faced is the aids inability to retain context beyond a few messages this made it difficult to have a coherent and meaningful conversation the ai often repeated responses and didn't fully comprehend the context of previous interactions leading to frustration on my part i understand that ai models have their limitations but i believe that enhancing the system's ability to maintain context could greatly improve the user experience an option feature where users can customize the aids behavior such as its role formatting and repetition would be highly beneficial moreover the aids responses sometimes lacked relevance to the given input and it appeared to generate content that didn't align with the specific requirements or instructions this hindered the effectiveness of the ai in providing accurate and useful information as a user i would appreciate more transparency and control over the aids behavior and responses as well as an improvement in its comprehension of complex interactions this would make the ai more userfriendly and increase its practical applications i understand that ai technology is continually evolving and i believe that with your expertise you can address these concerns and further enhance the capabilities of the ai language model thank you for considering my feedback i hope that this input contributes to the ongoing development of ai systems and their utility in various contents
